ID ORDER MANUFACTURING ENTERPRISES; MASS CUSTOMIZATION; FAMILY
   ARCHITECTURE; OPTIMIZATION; DESIGN; MODEL; MANAGEMENT; ALGORITHM
AB Reliability has been regarded as an evaluation criterion in production
   configuration, the key step in mass customization. In this article, the
   authors focus on the integration of reliability analysis and
   configuration at the component level. Possible failure causes obtained
   with a fault tree analysis (FTA) are mapped to the product
   configuration network model via a functional model and a limitation
   matrix. Next, when a configuration scheme is generated through
   intersection of a connection matrix and a generation matrix, its
   reliability can be achieved with the integrated FTA so to compare with
   those of other schemes in optimization. Such an integration method is
   also adaptable for situations where the original fault tree is changed,
   and several fault trees are involved together. Finally, an example of
   configuring a laptop computer is used to illustrate the whole
   integration process.
