AB Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) has proven useful in comparing the
   environmental impact of alternatives, life-cycle phases or parts in a
   product. To date, benchmarking a new product with previous
   environmental information entails a degree of subjectivity. This paper
   presents LCP-families, a concept to develop reference ranges for
   environmental impact of a new product. A new product can be catalogued
   as environmentally better or worse than a percentage of its
   competitors, depending on what position it occupies in its LCP-family.
   Three case studies of packaging products are carried out to show the
   applicability and usefulness of the concepts presented. (C) 2009
