TI Product family design and platform-based product development: a
   state-of-the-art review
SO JOURNAL OF INTELLIGENT MANUFACTURING
LA English
DT Review
DE product family; product platform; product architecture; customization;
   variety modularity; commonality; configuration
ID SUPPLY CHAIN DESIGN; MASS CUSTOMIZATION; CONFIGURATION-DESIGN;
   COORDINATING PRODUCT; MODULAR PRODUCTS; TO-ORDER; MANUFACTURING
   PROCESSES; DEVELOPMENT-PROJECTS; GENETIC ALGORITHM; VARIETY
AB Product family design and platform-based product development has
   received much attention over the last decade. This paper provides a
   comprehensive review of the state-of-the-art research in this field. A
   decision framework is introduced to reveal a holistic view of product
   family design and platform-based product development, encompassing both
   front-end and back-end issues. The review is organized according to
   various topics in relation to product families, including fundamental
   issues and definitions, product portfolio and product family
   positioning, platform-based product family design, manufacturing and
   production, as well as supply chain management. Major challenges and
   future research directions are also discussed.
